==English==
===Etymology===
The [[w:Belyando|Belyando]] is a river in western [[Queensland]].  The expression dates back to at least 1891 in a shearer's song.  (Reference: Wannan below.)
===Noun===
'''[[Belyando]] [[spew]]'''
# {{AU}} {{slang}} {{obsolete}} An illness afflicting [[shearer]]s, characterized by vomitting after meals.  Presumed to have been due to the hard work of shearing bent over in stifling heat.  (Reference: Bill Wannan, ''Australian Folklore'', Lansdowne Press, 1970, reprint 1979 ISBN 0-7018-1309-1.)
